latestPosts.caption:
An impromptu vacation. Gastronomic delight.Therapeutic. 🅶🅾🅰 was all of that.
Proof that it was a happy break? 
I have no insta worthy pics to put here, just a photo dump( literally!) that I'm sharing.

Journaling my Goa travel and some places worthy of visit for food lovers (especially seafood lovers) here:

- The best time to travel as per locals is Nov- Apr. Oct wasn't bad, warm yes. Shacks were not in full swing though we managed to visit 1 or 2.

- Taxis. The union is too strong to let aggregators come in. We rented a car for our stay. Happy to share number & fare details for ones who would want to.

- We stayed at a B&B at Candolim, run by a lovely couple. We chose an open villa as we didn't want a closed hotel stay. Anyone who would want more details, happy to answer on DM

- Attire- wore only cottons  I took my favourite jewellery pieces to accesorise.

- Food:
In most places, reservation is a tad difficult, do try and book them in advance if you get through the numbers

✔️Local shack food- pocket friendly beers and local food! Must try the -Xacuti and gambas pil pil.

✔️ Vinayak - for the ones who love local cuisine  We tried the special thalis(prawns/ fish& vegetarian one) which were satisfactory.

✔️ Andron - and my mouth waters just thinking back on this place. This not-so- famous - with tourists- restaurant, will satiate taste buds of real foodies. Haven for pork and beef lovers. Must must visit.

✔️Burger factory-  Loved the burger (cheddar+ bacon+ bbq sauce) and the milkshake (boozy banana) that I hogged. The fries were done well too.

✔️ The olive kitchen & Bar/ Antares - beautiful ambience, perfect for a sundowner, or for drinks. 

✔️ Gunpowder- the ambience is as lovely as I remember 5 years back. Food was enjoyable too.

✔️Cream Choc- for  those with a sweet tooth. Loved the bacio flavour gelato.

✔️ Baba Au Rhum, Felix, Bomras, Thalaasa, La Plage- were other recommendations which we did not visit as we wanted more local cuisines, but they stay added to the list,until next time ❤️

Hope my Goa sojourn helps the ones planning their next trip. Feel free to save, share and add to this
 
Happy weekend & festivities everyone 🎊
